# Conditional RBAC gating table (ILS-2352)
#
# Declarative data read by conditionalize-helm-rbac.awk. One row per gated rule.
# Pipe-separated columns (surrounding whitespace is trimmed):
#
#   file | kind | name | apiGroup | resources | action | helper
#
#   file      basename of the RBAC template the row applies to ("*" = any)
#   kind      document kind to match ("*"/"" = any)
#   name      metadata.name to match ("*"/"" = any) -- scopes "namespaces" so the
#             operator ClusterRole's own namespaces[get] rule stays unconditional
#   apiGroup  apiGroups entry to match ("" = core group)
#   resources resource to match; CSV for empty-guard = the rule's full resource set
#   action    block       -> wrap the whole matching rule
#             resource    -> wrap the single matching resource list item
#             empty-guard -> outer "or" wrapper around a rule whose every resource
#                            is individually gated (avoids an empty resources:)
#             whole-file  -> nest helper guard inside the file's createRBAC wrapper
#   helper    helper name (prefixed with ibm-licensing. at render time); for
#             empty-guard use "or:helperA,helperB"
#
# file                                  | kind        | name                            | apiGroup              | resources            | action       | helper
